{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=2007 |Team=South Carolina Gamecocks |Image=South Carolina Gamecocks wordmark.svg |ImageSize=150 |Conference=Southeastern Conference |Division=Eastern Division |ShortConference=SEC |CoachRank= |APRank= |BCSRank= |Record=6-6 |ConfRecord=3-5 |HeadCoach=[[Steve Spurrier]] |DefCoach=[[Tyrone Nix]] |StadiumArena=[[Williams-Brice Stadium]] (c. 80,250, grass) }} {{2007 SEC football standings}} The '''2007 South Carolina Gamecocks football team''' represented the [[University of South Carolina]] in the [[Southeastern Conference]] during the [[college football]] [[2007 NCAA Division I FBS football season|season of 2007-2008]]. The Gamecocks were led by [[Steve Spurrier]] in his third season as USC head coach and played their home games in [[Williams-Brice Stadium]] in [[Columbia, South Carolina]]. The team was bowl eligible at 6-6 but was not selected for a bowl game.
